        <updateDate>2009-04-03T21:36:22Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Older Worker Opportunity Act of 2009 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow employers who provide health and retirement benefits to their employees a tax credit for 25% of the first $6,000 of wages paid to individuals age 62 or older participating in a flexible work program. Terminates such credit after 2012. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
